assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. e x = e (-x)"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. o x = - o (-x)"
and h2 : "\<forall> x. e x + x powr 2 = o x"
and h3 : "\<forall> x. f x = e x + o x"
shows  "f 2 = -4"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem

\[e(x) + x^2 = o(x)\]for all $x.$  Let $f(x) = e(x) + o(x).$  Find $f(2).$ The final Answer is -4
 ### Proof
 Setting $x = -2,$ we get \[e(-2) + 4 = o(-2).\]Since $e(x)$ is even and $o(x)$ is odd, $e(-2) = e(2)$ and $o(-2) = -o(2),$ so \[e(2) + 4 = -o(2).\]Then $f(2)  = e(2) + o(2) = \boxed{-4}.$
 *)
